Description: Met  means no injury/harm identified or body system is stabilized/improved at time of evaluation
Not Met means injury/harm was identified or body system deteriorated or not as expected at time of evaluation
Ongoing  means the outcome needs further nursing intervention and should be evaluated at a later time
Unable to Assess means the outcome could not be evaluated due to unstable patient condition or emergent procedure
